1
00:00:09,333 --> 00:00:14,291
♪


2
00:01:39,083 --> 00:01:44,041
[CHILDREN chatter]

3
00:01:46,750 --> 00:01:48,625
[RIRIKO]
Ever since I was little,

4
00:01:48,708 --> 00:01:51,166
people have told me
that I'm a strange girl.

5
00:01:51,250 --> 00:01:52,041
Wanna play?

6
00:01:52,125 --> 00:01:53,125
Okay!

7
00:01:53,208 --> 00:01:53,875
Wow!

8
00:01:53,958 --> 00:01:55,375
Pretty, huh?

9
00:02:03,708 --> 00:02:06,958
[RIRIKO] For some reason,
I could never laugh with them.

10
00:02:13,166 --> 00:02:14,583
This is delicious!

11
00:02:14,666 --> 00:02:17,958
Oh, hey, look! It says
I have great luck!

12
00:02:18,041 --> 00:02:20,083
Yeah, I'm not really
loving mine.

13
00:02:20,166 --> 00:02:23,333
What's "a little lucky"?
Bring me another one, please.

14
00:02:23,416 --> 00:02:26,041
Hey, what's with all those tiny
little sips over there, huh?

15
00:02:26,125 --> 00:02:28,000
You gotta chug that thing, girl!
You gotta chug it!

16
00:02:28,083 --> 00:02:30,708
Regretfully, as Queen, I think
I should keep my wits about me

17
00:02:30,791 --> 00:02:32,958
in public and also keep
an eye on you guys.

18
00:02:33,041 --> 00:02:35,000
Are you kidding me?
What a bummer!

19
00:02:35,083 --> 00:02:38,333
Shiori, who does that?
Orange juice with your shiokara?

20
00:02:38,416 --> 00:02:40,125
Well, I'm the designated driver.

21
00:02:40,208 --> 00:02:42,708
And it's actually
not bad at all!

22
00:02:42,791 --> 00:02:43,916
[RIRIKO]
Urchin.

23
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:45,916
Soy sauce on pudding, right?

24
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:48,208
When I was little we used
to put honey on cucumbers

25
00:02:48,291 --> 00:02:49,916
and say it tasted like melon!

26
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:53,208
You can also put yogurt on
shiokara to make caviar.

27
00:02:53,291 --> 00:02:54,791
Seriously? Let's try it!

28
00:02:54,875 --> 00:02:57,458
Angelica, do you have
any yogurt back there?

29
00:02:58,833 --> 00:03:00,375
I have to go home, guys.

30
00:03:00,458 --> 00:03:02,416
What? Already?

31
00:03:05,750 --> 00:03:08,083
Thanks, Shi- <i>chan</i> . You didn't
have to leave with me.

32
00:03:08,166 --> 00:03:11,083
Oh, no, it's okay.
My grandpa worries, anyway.

33
00:03:11,166 --> 00:03:14,458
So, tell me. Did you actually
want to stay and hang out?

34
00:03:14,541 --> 00:03:16,041
I don't care.

35
00:03:16,125 --> 00:03:20,208
[SHIORI chuckles] You know,
you've really changed lately,

36
00:03:20,291 --> 00:03:23,833
since meeting Yoshi and
the girls. You're more cheerful.

37
00:03:23,916 --> 00:03:25,333
[RIRIKO gasps]

38
00:03:26,791 --> 00:03:30,166
I wonder. Is that really true?

39
00:03:33,541 --> 00:03:36,083
A Rural Romance in Manoyama.

40
00:03:36,166 --> 00:03:38,125
[USHIMATSU] It's sort of a
matchmaking tour and it's been

41
00:03:38,208 --> 00:03:41,333
organized by the singles in
the Community Club, locally.

42
00:03:41,416 --> 00:03:44,500
Hey, Yamada! You're in that
singles' group, right?

43
00:03:44,583 --> 00:03:47,125
Yeah. I mean, I have
a girlfriend, though.

44
00:03:47,208 --> 00:03:49,708
You held out on me?
Who is this girl?

45
00:03:49,791 --> 00:03:51,333
If she's hot,
I'm gonna kill you.

46
00:03:51,416 --> 00:03:53,583
[YAMADA] What are you even
talking about? You're married!

47
00:03:53,666 --> 00:03:56,083
Anyway, it appears that
there are only three females

48
00:03:56,166 --> 00:03:58,958
who have signed up for this
dang matchmaking tour thing.

49
00:03:59,041 --> 00:04:01,083
Kindaichi's the leader
of the singles' group,

50
00:04:01,166 --> 00:04:02,750
and came in here
crying about it.

51
00:04:02,833 --> 00:04:04,541
[KANEDA] Even if we're
only talking about three,

52
00:04:04,625 --> 00:04:06,541
we can't let them get away.

53
00:04:06,625 --> 00:04:09,250
How do we convince three city
girls to marry and settle

54
00:04:09,333 --> 00:04:11,458
here in Manoyama?

55
00:04:11,541 --> 00:04:13,166
So, he's pretty serious, then.

56
00:04:13,250 --> 00:04:15,791
[USHIMATSU] He is, and that's
where you come in, Queen.

57
00:04:15,875 --> 00:04:18,000
I don't care if there
are only three of them.

58
00:04:18,083 --> 00:04:20,416
I need you to figure out a
way to grab hold of these

59
00:04:20,500 --> 00:04:24,000
city girls' hearts and
not let them get away!

60
00:04:24,083 --> 00:04:26,541
[YOSHINO] So, what we need
to do is re-vamp the plan.

61
00:04:26,625 --> 00:04:28,583
We need to come up with
the perfect itinerary

62
00:04:28,666 --> 00:04:30,708
for this three-day,
two-night tour.

63
00:04:30,791 --> 00:04:33,666
Does anyone else here think that
we should start by re-naming it?

64
00:04:33,750 --> 00:04:36,125
totally agree with you
except for one thing:

65
00:04:36,208 --> 00:04:39,000
they've already been using
this name to advertise.

66
00:04:39,083 --> 00:04:40,791
Now, let's see. How 'bout
we go through the

67
00:04:40,875 --> 00:04:43,708
Community Club's
suggestions for activities.

68
00:04:43,791 --> 00:04:47,458
A karaoke duet tournament on
a rented, decked out party bus.

69
00:04:47,541 --> 00:04:49,333
A thrilling afternoon
of fortune-telling

70
00:04:49,416 --> 00:04:50,875
with lunch at Angelica's.

71
00:04:50,958 --> 00:04:54,083
Who will be connected by the
lovers' fated red somen?

72
00:04:54,166 --> 00:04:56,125
Show off your excellent
cooking skills.

73
00:04:56,208 --> 00:04:57,666
Compete in this
cooking challenge

74
00:04:57,750 --> 00:04:59,125
using local vegetables!

75
00:04:59,208 --> 00:05:01,916
The way to every prince's heart
is through his stomach?

76
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:03,750
Come and play the Chupa Game.

77
00:05:03,833 --> 00:05:06,375
One person is the Chupa,
and you must obey their orders.

78
00:05:06,458 --> 00:05:09,666
But if the Chupa issues orders
to the Hero, watch out?

79
00:05:09,750 --> 00:05:12,583
Were they seriously
going to do this stuff?

80
00:05:12,666 --> 00:05:13,791
[YOSHINO]
Hm...

81
00:05:17,166 --> 00:05:19,333
What kind of activities
would you want to do?

82
00:05:19,416 --> 00:05:22,458
Um. Well, the obvious thing
would be to go to all the

83
00:05:22,541 --> 00:05:24,166
tasty shops in town, right?

84
00:05:24,250 --> 00:05:26,875
I think it's probably best
to avoid this area, though.

85
00:05:26,958 --> 00:05:28,625
No, we've gotta be
honest and show them

86
00:05:28,708 --> 00:05:30,166
this place as it really is.

87
00:05:30,250 --> 00:05:32,041
We have to help them
fall completely in love

88
00:05:32,125 --> 00:05:33,833
with every part of Manoyama!

89
00:05:33,916 --> 00:05:36,333
How about if they stayed
in an old-style house?

90
00:05:36,416 --> 00:05:38,416
I think that can
be pretty charming.

91
00:05:38,500 --> 00:05:40,541
And I know no one's
taken my old place yet.

92
00:05:40,625 --> 00:05:42,250
That's such a great idea!

93
00:05:42,333 --> 00:05:44,916
We should give them experiences
they can't get anywhere else!

94
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:48,083
Exactly! Something creative
and filled with the discoveries

95
00:05:48,166 --> 00:05:50,583
and surprises you can
only get in the country!

96
00:05:50,666 --> 00:05:52,458
Hey, Rii- <i>chan</i> ,
you're the creative one.

97
00:05:52,541 --> 00:05:54,208
Do you have any brilliant ideas?

98
00:05:54,291 --> 00:05:56,208
A Get-Your-Blood-Sucked-
By-A-Leech tour?

99
00:05:56,291 --> 00:05:57,458
[YOSHINO, SHIORI gasp]

100
00:05:57,541 --> 00:05:59,708
Okay, that might be a
little bit too creative.

101
00:05:59,791 --> 00:06:01,833
What'd be the point of
having their blood sucked?

102
00:06:01,916 --> 00:06:04,666
A leech sucking out bad
blood is detoxifying.

103
00:06:04,750 --> 00:06:06,083
They use them in Ayurveda,

104
00:06:06,166 --> 00:06:08,250
a type of traditional
Indian medicine.

105
00:06:08,333 --> 00:06:10,083
You mean like
those doctor fish?

106
00:06:10,166 --> 00:06:12,291
I do think you're headed
in the right direction,

107
00:06:12,375 --> 00:06:15,083
but we might need to think
sparkly-shiny for these girls.

108
00:06:15,166 --> 00:06:17,625
Hey, this brewery's sake'
is pretty tasty stuff.

109
00:06:17,708 --> 00:06:19,166
What if we brought them here?

110
00:06:19,250 --> 00:06:20,958
Sake' really is
booming right now,

111
00:06:21,041 --> 00:06:22,666
so a tasting-tour might be good!

112
00:06:22,750 --> 00:06:24,208
Oh! See that mountain?

113
00:06:24,291 --> 00:06:26,250
There's a river on it
with so many fireflies,

114
00:06:26,333 --> 00:06:27,541
it's almost scary!

115
00:06:27,625 --> 00:06:29,541
I bet most city girls
would freak out over it!

116
00:06:29,625 --> 00:06:31,916
Oh, I would! A night
full of fireflies?

117
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:33,791
I thought bugs were
always out, for you.

118
00:06:33,875 --> 00:06:35,916
Well, yeah, they are,
but fireflies don't count.

119
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:38,916
Did you have a lot of fireflies
where you came from, Yoshino?

120
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:41,166
Definitely. I grew up
in a harbor town.

121
00:06:41,250 --> 00:06:43,375
Oh, cool! We should
go see them together!

122
00:06:43,458 --> 00:06:46,208
Like, scout it out for work,
and have a firefly sleepover!

123
00:06:46,291 --> 00:06:47,958
That sounds great! I love it!

124
00:06:48,041 --> 00:06:50,208
And you know, the bed next
to mine is always available!

125
00:06:50,291 --> 00:06:54,000
[SHIORI giggles] Aw!
Wait, what? I don't get it!

126
00:06:56,541 --> 00:06:59,125
Huh. Sake-tasting, fireflies,

127
00:06:59,208 --> 00:07:00,791
and a night in an
old-style house.

128
00:07:00,875 --> 00:07:02,541
Hm! Not bad at all, ladies.

129
00:07:02,625 --> 00:07:05,666
Thank you, but I can't help
thinking it's missing something.

130
00:07:05,750 --> 00:07:07,291
How about if they
got to spend a day

131
00:07:07,375 --> 00:07:08,958
as the head of the
Tourism Board?

132
00:07:09,041 --> 00:07:11,833
They can wear the Chupakabura
costume as much as they want!

133
00:07:11,916 --> 00:07:12,916
[SANAE]
What are we trying to do?

134
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:14,666
Show them a good time,
or punish them?

135
00:07:14,750 --> 00:07:15,916
[SHIORI]
You're right, though, Yoshi.

136
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:17,500
We need one more
thing on the agenda

137
00:07:17,583 --> 00:07:19,291
that really sells
them on the town.

138
00:07:19,375 --> 00:07:21,791
How about teaching them
the Manoyama Dance?

139
00:07:21,875 --> 00:07:23,291
What Manoyama Dance?

140
00:07:23,375 --> 00:07:24,625
Oh, it's lovely,

141
00:07:24,708 --> 00:07:26,666
and it's been passed down
here for generations.

142
00:07:26,750 --> 00:07:29,083
All the girls who grow up in
town are taught that dance

143
00:07:29,166 --> 00:07:30,458
in school when
they're very young.

144
00:07:30,541 --> 00:07:33,541
I remember that! I loved
learning it as a kid.

145
00:07:33,625 --> 00:07:36,250
Yep, I had to learn it back
when I was little, too.

146
00:07:36,333 --> 00:07:37,833
Is it really still a thing?

147
00:07:37,916 --> 00:07:41,416
This is so perfect! Exposure to
a local traditional art!

148
00:07:41,500 --> 00:07:43,666
We could give lessons
to the girls on the tour,

149
00:07:43,750 --> 00:07:46,083
then we can all dance
together at the end!

150
00:07:46,166 --> 00:07:47,958
Not me. I can't dance.

151
00:07:48,041 --> 00:07:49,916
Oh, don't worry
about that, Rii- <i>chan</i> !

152
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:51,666
I'm a terrible dancer, too!

153
00:07:51,750 --> 00:07:54,208
If we all practice together,
I'm sure we'll get it.

154
00:07:54,291 --> 00:07:57,208
Keep in mind, this dance has a
very long history in this town.

155
00:07:57,291 --> 00:07:58,833
Try to take it seriously.

156
00:07:58,916 --> 00:08:00,416
You just leave it to me!

157
00:08:00,500 --> 00:08:03,000
As queen, it's my duty to
learn it inside and out and

158
00:08:03,083 --> 00:08:04,541
make the town proud!

159
00:08:04,625 --> 00:08:06,958
I can be your dance teacher
if you'd like me to, Yoshino!

160
00:08:07,041 --> 00:08:09,750
[YOSHINO gasps]
Alright, my own tutor!

161
00:08:09,833 --> 00:08:13,166
I don't... think I'll be able
to dance like the Queen.

162
00:08:13,250 --> 00:08:15,041
[YOSHINO, SHIORI gasp]

163
00:08:15,125 --> 00:08:16,791
Oh, jeez, come on.

164
00:08:16,875 --> 00:08:19,333
You've always kind of avoided
this stuff, huh, Rii- <i>chan</i> ?

165
00:08:19,416 --> 00:08:20,750
You don't have to dance with us.

166
00:08:20,833 --> 00:08:23,000
We've probably got
it covered, no worries!

167
00:08:23,083 --> 00:08:24,916
[bell rings]

168
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:26,541
[RIRIKO]
It's time for me to head home.

169
00:08:26,625 --> 00:08:28,708
Okay! Why don't I
give you a ride?

170
00:08:28,791 --> 00:08:31,291
Thanks, but the buses
are still running.

171
00:08:31,375 --> 00:08:34,250
Would you accept the invitation
if I offered you a ride?

172
00:08:34,333 --> 00:08:35,833
[RIRIKO]
I...

173
00:08:35,916 --> 00:08:38,125
It's no problem at all,
and I'd like to, Rii- <i>chan</i> .

174
00:08:38,208 --> 00:08:39,250
Good night, then!

175
00:08:39,333 --> 00:08:40,250
See you tomorrow!

176
00:08:40,333 --> 00:08:42,416
Say hi to old granny.

177
00:08:43,916 --> 00:08:45,083
[KINU]
So, I'm curious.

178
00:08:45,166 --> 00:08:46,625
Why don't you want to
do the Manoyama Dance

179
00:08:46,708 --> 00:08:48,083
with the other girls?

180
00:08:48,166 --> 00:08:50,291
Mainly because I don't
like being told I have to

181
00:08:50,375 --> 00:08:52,750
do something just because
of some tradition.

182
00:08:52,833 --> 00:08:55,708
[KINU giggles] You sound
just like my husband.

183
00:08:55,791 --> 00:08:57,083
[RIRIKO]
Uh?

184
00:08:57,166 --> 00:08:59,041
Sorry, I shouldn't
have said that.

185
00:08:59,125 --> 00:09:02,041
I imagine it doesn't make
you happy to hear it.

186
00:09:02,125 --> 00:09:04,458
But, you see, I mean
it as a compliment.

187
00:09:04,541 --> 00:09:07,666
I like that you aren't
afraid to be an individual.

188
00:09:10,291 --> 00:09:12,416
[KINU]
Okay, hop on in.

189
00:09:16,458 --> 00:09:18,875
Good night. I'm heading out now.

190
00:09:18,958 --> 00:09:20,291
[CHITOSE]
Alright, good night.

191
00:09:20,375 --> 00:09:21,625
[RIRIKO]
I'm home.

192
00:09:21,708 --> 00:09:23,208
Well, hello there.

193
00:09:23,291 --> 00:09:27,166
I'm guessing Shi must have
given you a ride home?

194
00:09:27,250 --> 00:09:29,125
So you're helping out
with the Community Club's

195
00:09:29,208 --> 00:09:32,916
matchmaking tour. I feel sorry
for them because there's

196
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:35,458
no way that's going to go well.

197
00:09:35,541 --> 00:09:38,666
[RIRIKO] Grandma, do you
think I've changed?

198
00:09:38,750 --> 00:09:39,916
[CHITOSE]
Hm?

199
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:44,416
Why, has something
happened with you?

200
00:09:44,500 --> 00:09:46,416
You're still Ririko.

201
00:09:46,500 --> 00:09:49,083
And you're perfect
just the way you are.

202
00:09:51,416 --> 00:09:52,625
[YOSHINO]
What do you think?

203
00:09:52,708 --> 00:09:54,791
Did I maybe say something
I shouldn't have?

204
00:09:54,875 --> 00:09:57,458
No, and as long as you don't try
to force her to dance with us,

205
00:09:57,541 --> 00:09:59,125
I think it'll be fine.

206
00:09:59,208 --> 00:10:00,791
You and Rii- <i>chan</i>
have been pretty close

207
00:10:00,875 --> 00:10:02,291
since you were
little girls, right?

208
00:10:02,375 --> 00:10:03,750
[SHIORI]
Mm-hm!

209
00:10:03,833 --> 00:10:05,583
We've been friends since we
started elementary school.

210
00:10:05,666 --> 00:10:07,750
I wonder if Chitose
got angry with her

211
00:10:07,833 --> 00:10:09,958
when she didn't end up
learning the Manoyama Dance.

212
00:10:10,041 --> 00:10:12,625
She seems like she'd be
strict about that stuff.

213
00:10:12,708 --> 00:10:14,125
I know it's hard to believe,

214
00:10:14,208 --> 00:10:16,625
but granny Chitose is
pretty soft on Rii- <i>chan</i> .

215
00:10:16,708 --> 00:10:18,125
[YOSHINO]
Is she really?

216
00:10:18,208 --> 00:10:19,833
If she wasn't, she probably
wouldn't allow Rii- <i>chan</i>

217
00:10:19,916 --> 00:10:22,208
to do half the things
she does with us.

218
00:10:36,875 --> 00:10:38,250
It's a bunny, you see?

219
00:10:38,333 --> 00:10:40,083
It's cute!

220
00:10:40,166 --> 00:10:44,750
[SHIORI gasps]
What is that? A shrimp?

221
00:10:44,833 --> 00:10:46,625
[RIRIKO]
Anomalocaris.

222
00:10:46,708 --> 00:10:48,125
Anomama... no...

223
00:10:48,208 --> 00:10:49,875
Anomalocaris.

224
00:10:49,958 --> 00:10:51,750
Is it something
you can eat?

225
00:10:51,833 --> 00:10:53,333
No, not anymore.

226
00:10:53,416 --> 00:10:55,666
They've been extinct for
a very long time now.

227
00:10:55,750 --> 00:10:59,291
Oh, wow! You're like an
animal expert, Rii- <i>chan</i> !

228
00:10:59,375 --> 00:11:01,708
[gasps] Is it okay to
call you Rii- <i>chan</i> ?

229
00:11:01,791 --> 00:11:03,458
[RIRIKO]
Huh?

230
00:11:10,875 --> 00:11:14,416
[TEACHER]
Cheese! Smile for me, Ririko!

231
00:11:15,500 --> 00:11:16,875
[RIRIKO groans]

232
00:11:43,166 --> 00:11:44,041
[BOTH gasp]

233
00:11:44,125 --> 00:11:45,541
[WOMEN gasp]

234
00:11:47,666 --> 00:11:50,416
[YOSHINO] Are you here for the
Rural Romance Manoyama Tour?

235
00:11:50,500 --> 00:11:51,625
That's right!

236
00:11:51,708 --> 00:11:52,916
[YOSHINO]
Kiyomi Hiragi.

237
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:54,041
[KIYOMI chuckles]

238
00:11:54,125 --> 00:11:56,291
[YOSHINO]
Ayana Nakatsugawa.

239
00:11:56,375 --> 00:11:57,875
[YOSHINO]
And Izumi Koyama, right?

240
00:11:57,958 --> 00:11:59,333
Uh-huh!

241
00:11:59,416 --> 00:12:00,958
Welcome to Manoyama!

242
00:12:01,041 --> 00:12:04,416
My name is Yoshino Koharu,
Queen of Chupakabura.

243
00:12:04,500 --> 00:12:05,916
I'll be your tour guide!

244
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:08,750
And I'm her assistant,
Maki Midorikawa.

245
00:12:08,833 --> 00:12:11,208
[ALL]
It's very nice to meet you!

246
00:12:11,291 --> 00:12:13,583
[IZUMI] I was wondering,
is it just the three of us?

247
00:12:13,666 --> 00:12:14,875
Are we all that signed up?

248
00:12:14,958 --> 00:12:16,583
[YOSHINO]
Uh, yeah!

249
00:12:16,666 --> 00:12:19,583
We would've had to cancel it,
if any of you hadn't shown!

250
00:12:19,666 --> 00:12:21,125
[AYANA]
Uh... what?

251
00:12:21,208 --> 00:12:23,000
[YOSHINO] Uh, however! If you
focus on the positive side,

252
00:12:23,083 --> 00:12:25,000
it's like a reverse-harem!

253
00:12:25,083 --> 00:12:27,666
And you get your pick
of all the men in town!

254
00:12:32,708 --> 00:12:34,375
He's not too bad, right?

255
00:12:34,458 --> 00:12:36,208
Eh. Too old for my taste.

256
00:12:36,291 --> 00:12:39,166
[TAKAMIZAWA] Alright, alright,
ladies, I'm your driver today.

257
00:12:39,250 --> 00:12:42,458
However, if you princesses
need anything else, well...

258
00:12:42,541 --> 00:12:43,791
[ALL gasp]

259
00:12:43,875 --> 00:12:46,083
How gross! That didn't
actually work on you two!

260
00:12:46,166 --> 00:12:49,583
Takamizawa, you're a
married man! So, back off, sir!

261
00:12:49,666 --> 00:12:52,333
I should've known that he
would already have a wife.

262
00:12:52,416 --> 00:12:53,833
Don't worry!

263
00:12:53,916 --> 00:12:55,666
There are heaps of handsome
men from the Community Club

264
00:12:55,750 --> 00:12:57,583
just waiting for your arrival!

265
00:12:57,666 --> 00:13:00,291
Well, we can't guarantee
that "handsome" part, though.

266
00:13:00,375 --> 00:13:03,916
Okay, now seems like a good
time to go over the itinerary.

267
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:06,041
First, you have a welcome lunch!

268
00:13:12,333 --> 00:13:13,458
Ippei Taira.

269
00:13:13,541 --> 00:13:15,208
You can read my name
backwards and forwards

270
00:13:15,291 --> 00:13:20,541
and it's still the same name.
I'm 39. Work in non-profit.

271
00:13:20,625 --> 00:13:22,750
Hey, wait a minute,
I thought you were 42?

272
00:13:22,833 --> 00:13:25,416
So, this year's actually your
bad-luck year, isn't that right?

273
00:13:25,500 --> 00:13:27,291
No, didn't you know?
In Manoyama,

274
00:13:27,375 --> 00:13:29,625
they believe a man's
bad luck year is 39!

275
00:13:29,708 --> 00:13:30,625
[WOMEN giggle]

276
00:13:30,708 --> 00:13:32,041
I'm Kakimura.

277
00:13:32,125 --> 00:13:36,000
I grow Kabura and rice,
and I'm a young 33 years old!

278
00:13:36,083 --> 00:13:39,000
Hey, I'm Shibukawa.
I'm a former sushi chef.

279
00:13:39,083 --> 00:13:40,250
Former?

280
00:13:40,333 --> 00:13:42,916
I'm in training now to
be a competitive eater!

281
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:44,791
Uh, so... the thing is.

282
00:13:44,875 --> 00:13:46,666
The majority of the
Community Club members

283
00:13:46,750 --> 00:13:48,083
are at work during the day.

284
00:13:48,166 --> 00:13:49,708
So, for right now, we're going
to begin with the ones

285
00:13:49,791 --> 00:13:50,833
who could make it to lunch.

286
00:13:50,916 --> 00:13:52,041
--[door clatters]
--[bell rings]

287
00:13:52,125 --> 00:13:54,291
Hey, sorry I'm so late!

288
00:13:54,375 --> 00:13:56,916
Hello, dear brother. What on
earth brings you here today?

289
00:13:57,000 --> 00:13:59,916
Matchmaking! I'm a member
of the club. That okay?

290
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:01,916
Are you crazy?
You're still in high school.

291
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:03,791
But I'm graduating next year.

292
00:14:03,875 --> 00:14:05,291
Wait, shouldn't you be in class?

293
00:14:05,375 --> 00:14:07,166
No, not today! It's a holiday.

294
00:14:07,250 --> 00:14:09,291
Oh, he's still in
high school! What a cutie!

295
00:14:09,375 --> 00:14:11,291
Pretty sure that's
against the law.

296
00:14:11,375 --> 00:14:12,375
[IZUMI]
Huh?

297
00:14:12,458 --> 00:14:16,958
[ERIKA sighs]
You old desperate hags.

298
00:14:17,041 --> 00:14:19,958
Uh. Pardon me. What was that?

299
00:14:20,041 --> 00:14:22,208
Sorry for the wait!
I welcome you.

300
00:14:22,291 --> 00:14:24,375
Today's lunch is a
special dish, which I call

301
00:14:24,458 --> 00:14:26,625
"The Fated Red Threads" somen!

302
00:14:26,708 --> 00:14:28,208
Put your faith in the old legend

303
00:14:28,291 --> 00:14:31,458
and look to find who your
fated red somen leads to.

304
00:14:31,541 --> 00:14:33,541
You decided to go
with that, huh?

305
00:14:33,625 --> 00:14:38,583
♪

306
00:14:39,291 --> 00:14:40,333
So handsome!

307
00:14:40,416 --> 00:14:42,333
And Scandanavian!

308
00:14:44,416 --> 00:14:46,291
Subtle song choice.

309
00:14:47,791 --> 00:14:49,125
[YOSHINO]
Okay!

310
00:14:49,208 --> 00:14:51,166
I certainly hope you all
enjoyed your somen for lunch!

311
00:14:51,250 --> 00:14:53,958
Next up, we'll take a trip
around downtown Manoyama,

312
00:14:54,041 --> 00:14:55,916
and then visit the shopping
arcade where some members

313
00:14:56,000 --> 00:14:57,375
of the Community Club work.

314
00:14:57,458 --> 00:14:59,875
May I ask why Sandal is
coming along with us?

315
00:14:59,958 --> 00:15:01,875
Yeah, is he trying
to swoop in? Damn!

316
00:15:01,958 --> 00:15:02,958
Just calm down.

317
00:15:03,041 --> 00:15:04,958
We need to make
Manoyama more appealing,

318
00:15:05,041 --> 00:15:07,000
even if it means
getting his help.

319
00:15:07,083 --> 00:15:08,333
I mean, he can't steal them all.

320
00:15:08,416 --> 00:15:10,291
We'll just take
whoever's left over!

321
00:15:10,375 --> 00:15:12,791
Do you have absolutely
no sense of pride, man?

322
00:15:12,875 --> 00:15:15,166
Is he a member of the
Community Club, too?

323
00:15:15,250 --> 00:15:17,916
No, I'm fairly positive
that he's not.

324
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:19,708
Hey, Sandal, what're you--?

325
00:15:19,791 --> 00:15:22,041
You do realize this is a
matchmaking tour, right?

326
00:15:22,125 --> 00:15:24,291
Match Three master, here!

327
00:15:24,375 --> 00:15:27,416
Yeah, that's not exactly the
kind of match we're going for.

328
00:15:27,500 --> 00:15:30,458
Know what I'm best at?
Killing blue pieces.

329
00:15:33,000 --> 00:15:35,833
I hardly recognize the place.
There are ten times as many

330
00:15:35,916 --> 00:15:37,958
people here as
there usually are.

331
00:15:38,041 --> 00:15:39,541
[KANEDA] The single guys
in the Community Club

332
00:15:39,625 --> 00:15:43,000
from the next town over heard
rumors and came to check it out.

333
00:15:43,083 --> 00:15:45,333
Like a herd of beasts.

334
00:15:45,416 --> 00:15:49,041
[SHIORI] If only it was always
this lively around here, huh?

335
00:15:49,125 --> 00:15:52,333
[SANAE] Oh, Noge! The women are
coming, so you should move those

336
00:15:52,416 --> 00:15:54,416
magazines as far
back as possible.

337
00:15:54,500 --> 00:15:56,916
Do we really need
to be that careful?

338
00:15:57,000 --> 00:15:58,708
Now that I think about it,

339
00:15:58,791 --> 00:16:01,916
the Queen and you ministers
are women, too, you know!

340
00:16:02,000 --> 00:16:03,958
Why don't you drop the
tour stuff and marry a man

341
00:16:04,041 --> 00:16:05,041
from Manoyama?

342
00:16:05,125 --> 00:16:07,208
I'm still very focused
on my career.

343
00:16:07,291 --> 00:16:08,875
Don't think of it that way,

344
00:16:08,958 --> 00:16:11,166
as a choice between
career and marriage.

345
00:16:11,250 --> 00:16:12,500
[NOGE]
It's true.

346
00:16:12,583 --> 00:16:14,041
There's nothing wrong with
a stay-at-home husband.

347
00:16:14,125 --> 00:16:16,250
Oh, you're one of those guys
who would jump at the chance,

348
00:16:16,333 --> 00:16:16,833
aren't you?

349
00:16:16,916 --> 00:16:17,750
[SANAE sighs]

350
00:16:17,833 --> 00:16:19,833
[KANEDA gasps]
Here they are!

351
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:25,041
[NOGE, KANEDA gasp]

352
00:16:25,125 --> 00:16:26,666
They're cute.

353
00:16:28,791 --> 00:16:31,583
I'm Kindaichi, and I'm the
head of the singles group!

354
00:16:31,666 --> 00:16:33,458
It's a pleasure to
meet you ladies!

355
00:16:33,541 --> 00:16:36,375
Oh. What's this?

356
00:16:36,458 --> 00:16:38,458
[KIYOMI gasps]
Oh, it's red somen.

357
00:16:38,541 --> 00:16:40,208
It's what we had for lunch.

358
00:16:40,291 --> 00:16:43,458
It's like we're bound by this
red thread like the legend says.

359
00:16:43,541 --> 00:16:46,333
You gotta be kidding me. That
somen thing actually worked?

360
00:16:46,416 --> 00:16:49,208
It's not very romantic,
though, or is it?

361
00:16:49,291 --> 00:16:51,000
[KANEDA] When you need
directions, I'm your man!

362
00:16:51,083 --> 00:16:53,916
If there's one thing I know,
it's the local streets! Ha, ha.

363
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:55,333
[KIYOMI]
Thanks!

364
00:16:55,416 --> 00:16:56,208
[CHITOSE grunts]

365
00:16:56,291 --> 00:16:57,500
[door clatters]

366
00:16:57,583 --> 00:16:58,666
Huh?

367
00:17:02,333 --> 00:17:04,125
What, did something happen?

368
00:17:04,208 --> 00:17:05,625
[RIRIKO]
No, nothing.

369
00:17:05,708 --> 00:17:08,000
Have you eaten at
all yet, today?

370
00:17:08,083 --> 00:17:09,625
[RIRIKO]
Yes.

371
00:17:09,708 --> 00:17:11,208
Oh, is that true?

372
00:17:11,291 --> 00:17:12,875
[CHITOSE]
Sheesh!

373
00:17:12,958 --> 00:17:16,250
Why do they feel the need to
ship 'em in like this, anyway?

374
00:17:16,333 --> 00:17:18,000
Are you finished for the day?

375
00:17:18,083 --> 00:17:20,083
Next is a barbeque
at Sakura Pond.

376
00:17:20,166 --> 00:17:23,500
After that, we'll introduce them
to the Manoyama Dance.

377
00:17:23,583 --> 00:17:25,625
Are you dancing, too?

378
00:17:25,708 --> 00:17:27,125
No, I'm not.

379
00:17:27,208 --> 00:17:31,166
Okay, then. Why don't you
just come home early?

380
00:17:31,250 --> 00:17:32,416
[RIRIKO grunts]

381
00:17:42,750 --> 00:17:45,250
Were the three of you
already friends before this?

382
00:17:45,333 --> 00:17:46,958
Yeah, we're coworkers.

383
00:17:47,041 --> 00:17:49,875
Poor Kiyomi. She just had
her heart broken, didn't you?

384
00:17:49,958 --> 00:17:52,208
Hey, come on, Izumi.
That's really not cool.

385
00:17:52,291 --> 00:17:54,375
Don't worry, I'll make
you forget all about it!

386
00:17:54,458 --> 00:17:55,916
What, are you trying
to get a head start

387
00:17:56,000 --> 00:17:57,416
or something, Kindaichi?

388
00:17:57,500 --> 00:17:59,750
I can't believe people still
use come-on lines like that.

389
00:17:59,833 --> 00:18:01,125
It's so cheesy!

390
00:18:01,208 --> 00:18:03,500
Yeah, they don't even
use those on TV anymore.

391
00:18:03,583 --> 00:18:05,375
That makes it
kinda novel, though!

392
00:18:05,458 --> 00:18:06,375
Yeah, it does.

393
00:18:06,458 --> 00:18:07,416
[TAIRA gasps]

394
00:18:07,500 --> 00:18:08,750
You mean that
stuff's okay again?

395
00:18:08,833 --> 00:18:10,750
Well, in that case, I can
make her forget, too!

396
00:18:10,833 --> 00:18:13,458
Don't you think you should
maybe get a real job first?

397
00:18:13,541 --> 00:18:16,541
Oh, good! Looks like
they're having fun!xc

398
00:18:16,625 --> 00:18:18,583
I have to admit,
I was worried at first.

399
00:18:18,666 --> 00:18:20,708
But you didn't even
know what the tour was!

400
00:18:20,791 --> 00:18:22,458
I'm searching, you see.

401
00:18:22,541 --> 00:18:23,916
Uh?

402
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:25,583
I'm searching for a place.

403
00:18:25,666 --> 00:18:28,500
Where lovers have shared
their romantic moments.

404
00:18:28,583 --> 00:18:31,791
A memory from the
ever-so-distant past.

405
00:18:31,875 --> 00:18:33,458
Memory of...?

406
00:18:33,541 --> 00:18:37,958
I want to find proof.
Of how the two of them lived.

407
00:18:38,041 --> 00:18:41,000
[SHIORI]
Yoshi! Time to get started!

408
00:18:41,083 --> 00:18:42,541
Hurry up, come on!

409
00:18:42,625 --> 00:18:45,750
'Kay! I'll See you later,
Rii- <i>chan</i> . You good?

410
00:18:45,833 --> 00:18:47,000
[RIRIKO]
Mm-hm.

411
00:18:51,333 --> 00:18:56,291
♪

412
00:19:03,750 --> 00:19:05,875
Oh! The Manoyama Dance.

413
00:19:05,958 --> 00:19:08,750
It's a local dance, passed down
for many generations.

414
00:19:08,833 --> 00:19:09,875
[KIYOMI]
Uh-huh.

415
00:19:34,250 --> 00:19:35,750
I don't know if
they've told you,

416
00:19:35,833 --> 00:19:38,916
but long ago, a fearsome
dragon lived in Manoyama.

417
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:41,666
Hey, what're you trying to do?
Don't scare her, Kadota!

418
00:19:41,750 --> 00:19:43,541
Who says I'm trying
to scare her?

419
00:19:43,625 --> 00:19:45,541
I'm informing her of
an important lesson

420
00:19:45,625 --> 00:19:47,291
in Manoyama's history.

421
00:19:47,375 --> 00:19:49,583
I'm pretty sure there's
a stone dragon idol

422
00:19:49,666 --> 00:19:51,791
enshrined around
here someplace.

423
00:19:51,875 --> 00:19:53,166
[KIYOMI]
Really? A dragon?

424
00:19:53,250 --> 00:19:54,166
[USHIMATSU]
That's right.

425
00:19:54,250 --> 00:19:56,708
A dragon came here
from far away,

426
00:19:56,791 --> 00:19:58,500
and, taking the form
of a young woman,

427
00:19:58,583 --> 00:20:00,500
it made its nest in the pond.

428
00:20:00,583 --> 00:20:02,583
However, the dragon
hates revelry.

429
00:20:02,666 --> 00:20:05,583
That's why, when we dance
cheerfully and play music,

430
00:20:05,666 --> 00:20:07,708
the beast is kept at bay.

431
00:20:07,791 --> 00:20:11,041
So, the Manoyama Dance was
created in order to keep

432
00:20:11,125 --> 00:20:15,333
the dragon away from the town
for generations to come.

433
00:20:15,416 --> 00:20:17,250
[ALL giggle]

434
00:20:36,041 --> 00:20:37,458
[USHIMATSU]
Hm?

435
00:20:37,541 --> 00:20:38,708
[YOSHINO] Mr. Kadota!
Have you seen Rii- <i>chan</i> ?

436
00:20:38,791 --> 00:20:41,000
No, she seemed like
she wasn't feeling well,

437
00:20:41,083 --> 00:20:42,250
so maybe she left.

438
00:20:42,333 --> 00:20:43,750
I wonder if she's okay.

439
00:20:43,833 --> 00:20:46,291
I'll try texting her
a little later.

440
00:20:47,750 --> 00:20:48,791
What?

441
00:21:13,250 --> 00:21:14,583
[MAKI, SANAE yelp]

442
00:21:14,666 --> 00:21:16,166
[MEN groan]

443
00:21:16,250 --> 00:21:18,916
[ALL shout]

444
00:21:21,375 --> 00:21:23,791
I thought there wasn't rain
in the weather forecast!

445
00:21:23,875 --> 00:21:25,375
Yeah, I know!

446
00:21:25,458 --> 00:21:27,041
I'm pretty sure it said there
was only a ten percent chance.

447
00:21:27,125 --> 00:21:28,416
[NOGE sighs]
So, fun fact.

448
00:21:28,500 --> 00:21:30,500
The dragon that lives here
is actually a water god.

449
00:21:30,583 --> 00:21:33,000
You idiot! Are you trying
to make them anxious?

450
00:21:33,083 --> 00:21:36,833
Is this it? Is this the
stone idol Mr. Kadota

451
00:21:36,916 --> 00:21:38,916
was talking about before?

452
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:41,916
It looks like it hasn't been
taken care of in a long time.

453
00:21:42,000 --> 00:21:43,791
[ALL yelp]

454
00:21:46,125 --> 00:21:47,916
[ALL gasp]

455
00:21:48,000 --> 00:21:50,208
That's not good, you guys.

456
00:22:11,416 --> 00:22:16,375
♪

457
00:23:39,458 --> 00:23:42,375
[SANDAL] The matchmaking tour
really pissed off that dragon.

458
00:23:42,458 --> 00:23:45,250
I'm talking totally,
super-duper pissed.

459
00:23:45,333 --> 00:23:48,000
Next time:
"The Forgotten Requiem."

